  "open_methodology_risks": [
    "Famous landmarks (easy tier) are essentially memorized by frontier vision models — they reveal raw image-recognition only, not geolocation reasoning. The medium and hard tiers carry the real signal.",
    "Wikipedia REST summaries can change article images. Pre-fetched local cache freezes the bytes at corpus-pin time.",
    "A 15-image corpus is a smoke test, not a publishable result. v2 should grow to 100+ images and should follow IM2GPS3k indices for direct comparison with PIGEON / GeoCLIP."
  ]
